# Figma Layout Primitive Mapping

When translating Figma designs to code using `get_design_context`, map layout containers to DS primitives automatically based on the generated code's layout properties. Do NOT require designers to name layers after layout primitives.

## Decision Algorithm

For each container/frame in the Figma output, inspect the generated Tailwind/CSS classes or inline styles and apply the first matching rule:

### 1. Vertical stack (flex-direction: column)

Indicators: `flex-col`, `flex-direction: column`, vertical auto-layout

```tsx
import { Stack } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Stack gap="md">{children}</Stack>
```

### 2. Horizontal row (flex-direction: row)

Indicators: `flex-row`, `flex-direction: row`, `inline-flex`, horizontal auto-layout

```tsx
import { Inline } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Inline gap="sm">{children}</Inline>
```

Use `Group` only when `Inline` is not semantically appropriate (rare).

### 3. Grid layout

Indicators: `grid`, `grid-cols-*`, `grid-template-columns`, repeated equal-width children

```tsx
import { Grid } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Grid cols={{ base: 1, md: 2, lg: 3 }} spacing="lg">{children}</Grid>
```

Map `grid-cols-N` to `cols={N}`. For responsive grids, use breakpoint object syntax.

### 4. Container with padding only (no child flow)

Indicators: padding/background but no flex/grid on the frame itself, single child or content wrapper

```tsx
import { Box } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Box p="md" bg="gray.1">{children}</Box>
```

### 5. Centered content

Indicators: `items-center justify-center` on both axes, single child centered in frame

```tsx
import { Center } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Center h={200}>{children}</Center>
```

### 6. Page-level container

Indicators: max-width constraint, centered horizontally, page-level wrapper

```tsx
import { Container } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Container size="md">{children}</Container>
```

### 7. Advanced flex (responsive direction changes)

Indicators: direction changes across breakpoints, complex flex-wrap patterns

```tsx
import { Flex } from '@/components/DesignSystem';
<Flex direction={{ base: 'column', sm: 'row' }} gap="md">{children}</Flex>
```

### 8. Fallback

If none of the above patterns match (e.g., absolute positioning, no auto-layout), use `Box` with Mantine system props.

## Spacing Token Mapping

Map pixel values from Figma to DS spacing tokens:

| Figma Value | DS Token |
|-------------|----------|
| 4px         | `"xs"`   |
| 8px         | `"sm"`   |
| 16px        | `"md"`   |
| 24px        | `"lg"`   |
| 32px        | `"xl"`   |
| 48px        | `"xxl"`  |

If `get_variable_defs` returns a Figma spacing variable, resolve it to the closest DS token before using it.

For values between standard tokens, use the nearest token. For truly custom values, pass the numeric value directly (e.g., `gap={12}`).

## Alignment / Justify Mapping

| Tailwind / CSS                | DS Prop                       |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------|
| `items-start`                 | `align="flex-start"`          |
| `items-center`                | `align="center"`              |
| `items-end`                   | `align="flex-end"`            |
| `items-stretch`               | `align="stretch"`             |
| `justify-start`               | `justify="flex-start"`        |
| `justify-center`              | `justify="center"`            |
| `justify-end`                 | `justify="flex-end"`          |
| `justify-between`             | `justify="space-between"`     |
| `flex-wrap`                   | `wrap="wrap"`                 |

## Layer Name Overrides (backward compatibility)

If a Figma layer IS explicitly named after a layout primitive, honor that name:

- Layer named `Stack` -> `Stack`
- Layer named `Grid` -> `Grid`
- Layer named `Inline` -> `Inline`

This is an override, not a requirement. The auto-detection above should handle all other cases.

## Composing Nested Layouts

Real designs often nest multiple primitives. Apply the decision algorithm recursively:

```tsx
// Figma: vertical frame > horizontal frame > items
<Stack gap="lg">
  <Inline justify="space-between">
    <Title order={3}>Section</Title>
    <Badge>Status</Badge>
  </Inline>
  <Grid cols={{ base: 1, md: 2 }} spacing="md">
    <Card>...</Card>
    <Card>...</Card>
  </Grid>
</Stack>
```

## When to Read This Rule

This rule applies when:
- Implementing a design from a Figma URL
- The implement-design skill is translating `get_design_context` output
- Generating layout code from any Figma selection

For full layout guidance including edge cases, also read `components/DesignSystem/LAYOUT_GUIDE.md`.
